text:
Arachnophobia is a thing... and facing that fear in a controlled video game setting rather than hiding from it and letting it get stronger is MUCH healthier for you.

I have a fear of the ocean, and any wide open underwater segment in video games used to give me extreme anxiety. When Subnautica came out, I really wanted to play it, so I forced myself to play despite my fears. It was a struggle at first, but as I played, I got more and more comfortable being in that environment, to the point where I barely acknowledged it anymore. Now I can play anything with water and I have no fear.

So yeah, don't run from your phobias.
